The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Oil bonds boost IOC bottomline

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Good news

 New Delhi, Oct. 28: Indian Oil Corporation has clocked a net profit of Rs 3,050 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2006, after receiving oil bonds to the tune of Rs 7,168 crore from the government. 

 The company had posted a net profit of Rs 948.96 crore for the same quarter of the previous fiscal. 

 For the first six months ended September 30, the companys net profit works out to Rs 4,831 crore against Rs 891 crore for the same period of the previous year. 

 The first-half net profit takes into account Rs 7,168 crore that the company received as oil bonds as partial compensation for under-recoveries on LPG, kerosene, petrol and diesel. It also includes a one-time capital gain of Rs 3,225 crore on the sale of 20 per cent equity investment in ONGC during the first quarter. 

 The gross turnover of the company during the second quarter went up 26.3 per cent to Rs 58,384.12 crore from Rs 40647.48 crore in the same quarter of 2005.

 IOC chairman Sarthak Behuria said the company still had under-recoveries to the tune of Rs 2,462 crore for the first half of the current fiscal. However, this is lower than the corresponding figure of Rs 5,627 crore for the previous year.

 Behuria said throughput of Indian Oils refineries and pipelines network was 20.54 million tonnes and 24.38 million tonnes, respectively, for the same period compared with 18.57 million tonnes and 22.08 million tonnes, respectively, in the previous year.

 Nestle net rises 11%

 Nestle India today posted an 11.24 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 82.98 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 74.59 crore during the corresponding period a year ago.

 Total income (net of excise) has increased 15.36 per cent to Rs 727.33 crore for the third quarter this fiscal against Rs 630.48 crore for the same period of the previous year, the company said.

 Tata Elxsi

 Software services provider Tata Elxsi today posted a 39.22 per cent increase in profit after tax at Rs 11.89 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 8.54 crore in the corresponding quarter in 2005-06. Total income increased 33.83 per cent to Rs 75.12 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 56.13 crore in the same quarter last year. 




